in cuts diplomatic ties with Iran|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/01/iran-accuses-saudi-arabia-fuelling-tensions-160104074825179.html|accessdate=14 April 2017|agency=Al Jazeera|date=4 January 2016}}</ref>\n* [[2017 Lebanon\u2013Saudi Arabia dispute]] \u2013 Saudi Arabia suspend military aid to [[Lebanon]] over alleged [[Hezbollah|Iranian influence]] and the country's refusal to condemn the [[2016 attack on the Saudi diplomatic missions in Iran|attack on Saudi embassy]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Saudi Arabia and Gulf allies warn against Lebanon travel|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-35649433|accessdate=12 July 2017|agency=BBC News|date=24 February 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Ahvaz military parade attack]]\n* [[2019 Abqaiq\u2013Khurais attack]]\n* [[2019\u20132020 Persian Gulf crisis]]\n}}\n| combatants_header =\n| combatant1  = {{plainlist}}\n{{flagicon|Iran}} '''[[Iran]]'''\n* ''Proxies'':\n* [[Hezbollah Al-Hejaz]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Daoud|first=David|url=http://www.thetower.org/article/meet-the-proxies-how-iran-spreads-its-empire-through-terrorist-militias/|title=Meet the Proxies: How Iran Spreads Its Empire through Terrorist Militias|date=March 2015|issue=24|work=The Tower Magazine|accessdate=18 August 2016}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon image|Logo of the Organization for the Islamic Revolution in the Arabian peninsula.svg}} [[Organization for the Islamic Revolution in the Arabian Peninsula|OIRAP]]<ref>{{citation|last=Hashim|first=Ahmed Salah|url=https://www.rsis.edu.sg/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/CO16022.pdf|title=Saudi-Iranian Rivalry and Conflict: Shia Province as Casus Belli?|date=29 January 2016|number=22|journal=RSIS Commentary|publisher=S. Rajaratnam School of International Studies|accessdate=18 August 2016}}</ref> <small>(1979\u20131991)</small><ref name=\"atimes.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.atimes.com/atimes/Middle_East/HJ26Ak02.html|title=Saudi Shi'ites: New light on an old divide|first=Mahan|last=Abedin|work=[[Asia Times]]|date=26 October 2006|access