ck|title=Qatar: UAE and Saudi Arabia step up pressure in diplomatic crisis|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/jun/07/qatar-fbi-says-russian-hackers-planted-fake-news-story-that-led-to-crisis-report|accessdate=7 March 2018|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=7 June 2017}}</ref>\n* [[2011 alleged Iran assassination plot]]\n* Saudi-led formation of the [[Islamic Military Alliance]] (which excludes Iran, Iraq and Syria) in 2015\n* [[Execution of Nimr al-Nimr]] and [[2016 Saudi Arabia mass execution|47 others]] by Saudi Arabia in 2016\n* Attack on [[2016 attack on the Saudi diplomatic missions in Iran|Saudi Arabian embassy in Tehran]] and the consulate in Mashhad\n* Bahrain and Saudi Arabia sever diplomatic relations with Iran in January 2016<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chulov|first1=Martin|title=Saudi Arabia cuts diplomatic ties with Iran after execution of cleric|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/jan/03/saudi-arabia-cuts-diplomatic-ties-with-iran-after-nimr-execution|work=The Guardian|date=4 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bahrain cuts diplomatic ties with Iran|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/01/iran-accuses-saudi-arabia-fuelling-tensions-160104074825179.html|accessdate=14 April 2017|agency=Al Jazeera|date=4 January 2016}}</ref>\n* [[2017 Lebanon\u2013Saudi Arabia dispute]] \u2013 Saudi Arabia suspend military aid to [[Lebanon]] over alleged [[Hezbollah|Iranian influence]] and the country's refusal to condemn the [[2016 attack on the Saudi diplomatic missions in Iran|attack on Saudi embassy]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Saudi Arabia and Gulf allies warn against Lebanon travel|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-35649433|accessdate=12 July 2017|agency=BBC News|date=24 February 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Ahvaz military parade attack]]\n* [[2019 Abqaiq\u2013Khurais attack]]\n* [[2019\u20132020 Persian Gulf crisis]]\n}}\n| combatants_header =\n| combatant1  = {{plainlist}}\n{{flagicon|Iran}} '''[[Iran]]'''\n* ''Proxies'':\n* [[Hezbollah Al-Hejaz]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Daoud|first=David|url=http://www.thetower.org/article/meet-the-proxies-how-iran-spreads-its-empire-through-terrorist-militias/|title=Meet the Proxies: How Iran Spreads Its Empire through Terrorist Militias|date=March 2015|issue=24|work=The Tower Magazine|accessdate=18 August 2016}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon image|Logo of the Organization for the Islamic Revolution in the Arabian peninsula.svg}} [[Organization for the Islamic Revolution in the Arabian Peninsula|OIRAP]]<ref>{{citation|last=Hashim|first=Ahmed Salah|url=https://www.rsis.edu.sg/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/CO16022.pdf|title=Saudi-Iranian Rivalry and Conflict: Shia Province as Casus Belli?|date=29 January 2016|number=22|journal=RSIS Commentary|publisher=S. Rajaratnam School of International Studies|accessdate=18 August 2016}}</ref> <small>(1979\u20131991)</small><ref name=\"atimes.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.atimes.com/atimes/Middle_East/HJ26Ak02.html|title=Saudi Shi'ites: New light on an old divide|first=Mahan|last=Abedin|work=[[Asia Times]]|date=26 October 2006|accessdate=24 April 2017}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon image|Fatemiyoun Seal.svg}} [[Liwa Fatemiyoun]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mashal|first1=Mujib|last2=Faizi|first2=Fatima |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/11/world/asia/afghanistan-iran-syria-revolutionary-guards.html|title=Iran Sent Them to Syria. Now Afghan Fighters Are a Worry at Home.|work=The New York Times|date=11 November 2017|access-date=4 February 2019}}</ref>\n{{endplainlist}}\n| combatant1a = '''[[Bahraini uprising of 2011|Bahraini uprising]]''' (2011\u201314)\n{{plainlist}}\n{{flagdeco|Bahrain}} [[Bahraini opposition]]\n{{endplainlist}}\n| combatant1b = '''[[Syrian Civil War]]''' (2011\u2013present)\n{{plainlist}}\n{{SYR}}<br />\n{{flagicon image|InfoboxHez.PNG}} [[Hezbollah]]<br />\n{{RUS}}<br />\n{{flagdeco|IRQ}} [[Popular Mobilization Forces (Iraq)|PMF]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.alwatanvoice.com/arabic/news/2015/07/03/738470.html|title=\u0627\u0644\u062d\u0634\u062f \u0627\